+## 4. Technical Stack
+
+**Framework:** Astro 4.0+
+- Ships **zero JavaScript by default** - optimal performance
+- **Islands architecture** - static content stays static, only globe is interactive
+- Built-in MDX support for blog
+- Excellent SEO with static site generation
+- Framework agnostic (can use React only where needed)
+- Built-in image optimization
+- Deploy anywhere (Vercel, Netlify, Cloudflare)
+
+**3D Globe (React Island):**
+- **React Three Fiber** - Declarative 3D with React (only loaded for globe)
+- **Three.js** - WebGL 3D graphics engine
+- **@react-three/drei** - Helpers (OrbitControls, etc.)
+- **react-globe.gl** - Pre-built globe component (evaluate vs custom)
+
+**Animation & Styling:**
+- **Tailwind CSS** - Utility-first styling
+- **GSAP ScrollTrigger** - Lightweight parallax effects
+- **Framer Motion** (optional) - Page transitions if needed
+- CSS animations for simple effects
+
+**Content:**
+- **MDX** - Blog posts in Markdown with components (built into Astro)
+- Frontmatter for metadata (title, date, tags, etc.)
+- Content collections for type-safe content
+
+**Other:**
+- TypeScript
+- ESLint + Prettier
+- Vercel/Netlify Analytics (privacy-friendly)
+
+**Why This Stack:**
+
+1. **Performance First** - Astro ships minimal JS, perfect for "wow" first impression
+2. **Islands Architecture** - Only the 3D globe needs heavy JS, everything else is static HTML
+3. **Content-Heavy Site** - Blog, projects, bookshelf are all static content (Astro's strength)
+4. **Mobile Performance** - 54% of traffic is mobile, Astro excels here
+5. **SEO** - Static generation with no client-side routing overhead
+6. **Future-Proof** - Can add serverless functions or backend later if needed
+7. **Simplicity** - No backend complexity we don't need
+
+**Architecture:**
+```
+Astro (base)
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Static Pages: About, Projects, Blog, Bookshelf, Contact (zero JS)
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ 3D Globe: React island with Three.js (only this loads JS)
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Parallax: GSAP for scroll effects (minimal JS)
+‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Content: MDX files for blog posts
+```
+
+**Technical Implementation Notes:**
+- Globe as client-only React island (`client:load` or `client:visible`)
+- Custom green/blue planet texture mapping
+- Pin markers: 3D objects or HTML overlays on globe
+- OrbitControls for rotation, raycasting for pin clicks
+- Level-of-detail optimization for mobile
+- Lazy load 3D assets for performance
+- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for accessibility
+- Dark mode default (space theme), light mode = daytime planet
+- No backend needed - use services (Formspree for contact, etc.)
